 HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaniera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/19/02 1:46:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1888.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What is the best way to raise sneak? (N/T)</span><hr size=1> I know this one, I know this one !!!<br><br>I dont' know if you know this, but you don't have to be standing for your sneak skill to go up. So, when you have a big fight and you have to sit to regain health, or your caster needs mana so you're waiting to fight, or you're running to a zone, just keep hitting sneak.  Your skill will go up so easy it's just not funny!<br><br>I hit my sneak button in tandem with Sense heading...I find that I hit sneak, I can press sense heading 3-4 times waiting for sneak to recycle. Kinda nice to build up two skills at once <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Aniera<br>11 Monk of Quellious<br>Wife of Griefo, Shaman of Halas<br>Mith Marr Server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unorpin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Norpin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand High Poobah</span><br>  Posts: 4068<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/19/02 4:42:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1888.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What is the best way to raise sneak? (N/T)</span><hr size=1> &quot;I dont' know if you know this, but you don't have to be standing for your sneak skill to go up.&quot;<br><br>That's a good point Aniera, I sometimes forget that this sort of thing isn't obvious to people who are new to the skill. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulyane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lyane</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/19/02 11:47:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1888.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What is the best way to raise sneak? (N/T)</span><hr size=1> For rogues, after 101 skill in sneak it never fails anymore. I believe it is the same with the monkly sneak, it has never failed on my monk at least after mastering the skill. <br><br>Sneak is one of the skills I miss the most on alts without it, being able to shop anywhere is very convenient. <br><br>Lyane Peredhel<br>Fennin Ro <p><center><p>It's not good to let any kid near a container that has a skull and crossbones on it, because there might be a skeleton costume inside and the kid could put it on and really scare you. <br>--Deep Thoughts by Jack Handey </p></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=fopoodzo>Fopoodzo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 720<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/20/02 4:11:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1888.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What is the best way to raise sneak? (N/T)</span><hr size=1> You can tie it to a movement key with a macro (along with SH, ID and FD..... although I don't think all at once <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udakkin2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dakkin2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/20/02 4:20:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1888.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What is the best way to raise sneak? (N/T)</span><hr size=1> It depends what you mean by &quot;best&quot; Karhik I'm afraid.<br><br>The least troublesome way is to hammer sneak off and on repeatedly during downtime as the people above suggested.<br><br>If you want to get as many skills as you can in working order as soon as you hit level 17 and get Feign Death, you'll probably need to spend around 6 hours raising them together, which takes much less time overall than maxing the skills individually:<br><br>Find a secluded spot where you can run round in circles and fall a little way (a steep hillside or the end of some kind of ledge), then do this while hitting sneak, FD, sense heading and maybe even mend and instill doubt over and over.<br><br>This way, you use the same time you invest in raising sneak to raise feign death, sense heading, mend and ID all at once.<br><br>I hope this helps,<br><br>Dak <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uargfeld.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Argfeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 445<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/20/02 6:48:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1888.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What is the best way to raise sneak? (N/T)</span><hr size=1> One way I did it was to double tap the sneak hotkey while travelling every time it ungreyed.  The double tap puts you into sneak mode and then immediately takes you out of it, so you don't slow down.  <br><br>Another thing I did was to make a hotkey for a bunch of the more tedious non-combat skills, such as sense heading and FD and sneak.  If I remember correctly, the hotkey would activate sense heading, activate sneak, activate FD, turn off sneak, and then cause me to stand back up.  I would find one of those tents out in the desert that is just large enough to give you a safe fall check and run up it and jump off, hit the hotkey, run up tent, jump off, hit hotkey, etc., etc.<br> <p>Argfeld<BR>Level 58 Monk<BR>Order of the Scattered Winds<BR>Bertoxxulous<BR><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uxirys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xirys</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 93<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/20/02 8:39:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1888.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What is the best way to raise sneak? (N/T)</span><hr size=1> My own method was after fighting, I'd FD, Sneak, Bind Wounds. Kept all three skills rising up nicely, and naturally without having to session on one of the skills. <p>Oderint Dum Metuant - Let them hate, as long as they fear... -  <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=2735>Xirys</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uz0nk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Z0nk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/20/02 9:33:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1888.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What is the best way to raise sneak? (N/T)</span><hr size=1> I did the same as X above...  FD, bind wounds, sneak on, sneak off...  All three have the exact same cycle time...  I also double tapped sneak while running to and from my hunting spot...  Now that sneak is maxed, I still FD, then BW when I need to BW... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uiagomonk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>iagomonk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 968<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/23/02 8:56:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1888.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Attention new monks</span><hr size=1> For the love of god and all that is holy, if you're training FD in your downtime (waiting for a port, standing around in the bazaar etc) please do NOT stand up between FD.  Your skill will still go up if you feign again while you're on the ground, and you won't make that annoying death noise every 6 seconds. <p>Brother Iago<BR>Grandmaster of Quellious<BR>Emerald Templars<BR><I>"Wu's your daddy?"</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaniera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/23/02 9:37:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1888.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Now that's useful info !!!</span><hr size=1> I'm still 5 levels away from getting FD, but I hadn't realized that you don't have to stand back up to get the skill increase.  When I get the FD skill, It's nice to know that I won't be a nuisance practicing around other players !<br><br>Thanks Much !!<br>Ani <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukorph.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Korph</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 180<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/24/02 4:37:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1888.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Now that's useful info !!!</span><hr size=1> A little bit of information to add:  For monks, Sneak caps at 113 skill. <p>-Korph<br><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=308735"><img src="http://gjband.com/Sig.jpg"><br>Level 51 Disciple</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukarhik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karhik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/29/02 12:05:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1888.topic&index=13>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:</span><hr size=1> Thanks, all. I didn't know it capped at 113, so that is some good info. <br><br>I just wondered, because it didn't look like my sneak was going up much, I wondered if you had to be in range of someone whom it affected or what.<br><br>I'll keep mashing that hotkey <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showPrevMessage?topicID=1888.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showNextMessage?topicID=1888.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1888.topic&index=13><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.emailToFriend?topicID=1888.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.threadControl?topicID=1888.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusine